Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of
@water{} to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the spaghetti.

Peel and grate the @garlic{3%cloves}(peeled) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Lay the @salmon fillets{2}, skin-side down, onto a lined #baking tray{}. Spread
half of the garlic over the fillets and season with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until cooked through,
~{10-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling
raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim the bottom 2cm from the @asparagus{100%g} and discard. Cut
into thirds.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @spaghetti{180%g} and bring back to
the boil. Cook until tender, ~{8%minutes}.

When the pasta has 2 mins left, add the asparagus to the same pan to cook for
the remaining time.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with
@olive oil{1%tbsp} and stir through to stop the pasta sticking together.

Meanwhile, zest and halve the @lemon{1}. Pick the @tarragon{1} leaves from
their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @panko breadcrumbs{10%g}. Season with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{} and fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted,
~{3-4%minutes}.

> Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Once cooked, transfer the toasted crumbs to a small #bowl{}, then set your
pangrattato aside.

Pop the (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of
@olive oil{1%tsp}. Once hot, add the garlic and half the chopped tarragon.
Fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and
@water for the sauce{100%ml}. Simmer until piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, chop the @tomato{1%medium}(chopped into 1cm chunks).

Squeeze half the lemon juice into a medium bowl. Add @olive oil{} and
@honey{1%tsp}, then season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Stir the
tomato chunks through the dressing and set aside.

Once the salmon is cooked, gently peel off the skin and flake apart the flesh
with a #fork{} into bite-sized pieces.

Stir the cooked pasta, asparagus, flaked salmon, remaining tarragon and
@grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} into the sauce.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and add a good squeeze of lemon
juice. Add a splash of water to loosen if needed.

When everything's ready, add the @wild rocket{20%g} to the bowl of tomatoes and
toss to coat in the dressing.

Stir the lemon zest through the pangrattato.

Share the salmon pasta between your bowls and sprinkle over the zesty
pangrattato.

Serve with the salad and any remaining lemon cut into wedges alongside.

Enjoy!